I like to keep my date formats all together, instead of having <code>.strftime()</code> mixed into my code.
<!--more-->
Create a file <code>/config/initializers/custom_date_formats.rb</code>

Load your formats into <code>Time::DATE_FORMATS</code>
<% code('ruby') do %>Time::DATE_FORMATS[:ymd] = "%Y-%m-%d"<% end %>

Use like so:
<% code('ruby') do %>@christmas_post.created_at.to_s(:ymd)
# => "2009-12-25"</pre>
